  // What is Dance Section (Point 1 - SEO CRITICAL)
  danzaBarcelona_whatIs_title: 'What is Classical and Contemporary Dance?',
  danzaBarcelona_whatIs_definition:
    'Classical and contemporary dance are artistic disciplines that combine technique, body expression and scenic art. Classical Ballet is the technical foundation of all dances: posture, alignment, placement, turnout, extension, control and universal vocabulary of steps. Contemporary Dance emerged as an evolution of classical ballet and modern dance, incorporating floor movements, fluidity, weight, gravity and emotional expression without academic limits.',
  danzaBarcelona_whatIs_schools:
    "There are different classical ballet schools: the Russian School (Vaganova), the French School (Cecchetti), the Italian School, the English School (Royal Academy of Dance) and the Cuban School. At Farray's Center we teach the Cuban School of Ballet, recognized worldwide for combining Russian technical rigor with Caribbean musicality, expressiveness and physical strength.",
  danzaBarcelona_whatIs_contemporary_title: 'What is Contemporary Dance?',
  danzaBarcelona_whatIs_contemporary_text:
    'Contemporary Dance is a free style that fuses classical ballet, modern dance, floor work techniques, release, contact improvisation and emotional expression. It allows exploring organic movements, body weight, controlled falls, improvisation and personal narrative. Perfect for those seeking expressive freedom with technical foundation.',
  danzaBarcelona_whatIs_benefits:
    "Studying classical and contemporary dance improves posture, flexibility, muscle strength, coordination, musicality, mental discipline and self-esteem. It's a complete physical activity that works body and mind, develops versatile artists and prepares for professional auditions, dance companies, musicals and stage careers.",

